{
  "stem": "802.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not all of them, but those Jews who had been born in Poland, who emigrated to Germany, were sent back to Poland.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So that were the first signs.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Among the first signs were also-- I remember my parents were glued to the radio always-- speeches of Hitler that they were able to catch on the radio.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the anti-Semitism in Poland was encouraged by virtue of what was going on in Germany.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There were many anti-Semites in Poland, which is not to say that there were not many decent Poles, you know.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I don't want to smear everyone with the same brush.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I'm sure there were some decent Poles.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Some saved Jews here and there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Not too many, which shows that more could have done it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "You know, if a few were able to save, more could have done it, too.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it seems to me that I was aware of anti-Semitism virtually since I was born.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was an integral part of our existence.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know, Jews are not equal to Christians, you know.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Although we always thought the other way around.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You know, we always felt that we're OK.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Nonetheless, it is very difficult to extricate yourself from this notion that is constantly pressed upon you that you are not as good as the others.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So there was a measure of shame in being Jewish, too.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "For example, if you were blonde, it was a boon, but it was also a-- and it was also a compliment.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Even now, when I speak sometimes with my survivor friends, they say, well, they could not recognize me because I had blonde hair and blue eyes, as if it were-- as if it were a compliment.",
      "word_count": 36
    }
  ],
